In above experiments, we had accomplished color change from orange to green to colorless and from orange to green to blue as the signal response. Based on the effect of Cys on Cu2+, we further achieved the color change from orange to green to colorless to green to blue and displayed by fluorescence spectroscopy (Fig. 8
                        a). In addition, changing order of addition achieved the color change from orange to green to blue to colorless to blue (Fig. 8b). The logical relationship diagram be obtained in Fig. 8c and d, which shows the relationship between adding order and amount and fluorescence. Mechanisms and processes are illustrated in Scheme S2 (Scheme 3
                        ).
